---
Source:
  - Title: Treasury of Traditional Wisdom
    Page: 90
By: Swâmi Brahmânanda
Tags:
  - Sacrifice-Death=Illusion=The Hold of Passion
  - Sacrifice-Death=Renunciation-Detachment=Indifference to Pleasure and Pain
---
The world is so constructed, that if you wish to enjoy its pleasures, you
must also endure its pains. Whether you like it or not, you cannot have one
without the other.
